# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-operational-contract
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Define the operational contract between the builder, ansible automation, and
#   cluster nodes. This ensures predictable, safe, and reproducible operations.
#
# Contract Terms:
#
#   1. Builder Responsibilities
#      - Produce verified kernel artifacts
#      - Maintain build metadata
#      - Follow prechecks and postchecks
#
#   2. Ansible Responsibilities
#      - Deploy kernels safely
      - Run diagnostics
      - Maintain cluster health
#
#   3. Node Responsibilities
#      - Run distccd
#      - Execute workloads
#      - Report health
#
#   4. Shared Responsibilities
#      - Maintain integrity
#      - Follow rollback-first philosophy
#      - Keep documentation ASCII-safe and reproducible
#
# Notes:
#   - This file defines the authoritative operational contract.
# =============================================================================
